      • getSourceAsEntity

        public Entity getSourceAsEntity()
        Get the source of the damage done as an instance of Entity.

        If the damager related to this data is an instance of Projectile, this method will return the shooter of that projectile, assuming it is an instance of Entity. To get the projectile instance itself, use getSourceAsProjectile().

        Returns:
        The source of damage, or null if it is not an entity that dealt the damage.

      • getSourceAsBlock

        public Block getSourceAsBlock()
        Get the source of the damage done as an instance of Block.

        If the damager related to this data is an instance of Projectile, this method will return the block represented by the shooter of that projectile, assuming it is an instance of BlockProjectileSource. To get the projectile instance itself, use getSourceAsProjectile().

        Returns:
        The source of damage, or null if it is not a block that dealt the damage.

      • getSourceAsProjectile

        public Projectile getSourceAsProjectile()

        Returns:
        The source of damage, or null if it is not a projectile that dealt the damage.

      • setDamageAmount

        public void setDamageAmount(double amount)
        Sets the final amount of damage dealt by this source, as known by the store.

        This value is intended to be decreased by using this setter if health lost by this damage event is regenerated.

        This setter method will round incoming values to the nearest 100th decimal place.

        Parameters:
        amount - The new amount.
        See Also:
        Math.rint(double)
